	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Wla byte defining</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For my game, I really need to do something like this:
<br />
<br />.db #&lt;Lable, #&gt;Lable
<br />
<br />#&gt;Lable: High address of Lable
<br />#&lt;Lable: Low address of Lable
<br />
<br />But WLA doesn't seem to support that. Is there a way to define bytes as the High/Low addresses of a lable?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>dXtr</b> [ Mon Jun 25, 2007 3:16 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />according to the docs it do support &lt; and &gt;
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The following operators are valid:<br /><br />(, ), | (or), &amp; (and), ^ (power), &lt;&lt; (shift left), &gt;&gt; (shift right), +, -,<br /># (modulo), ~ (xor), *, /, &lt; (get the low byte) and &gt; (get the high byte).<br /></div>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


