		<td><b>Re: Wla byte defining</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">.db #&lt;Lable, #&gt;Lable</div>
<br />The "#" should only be used for immediate addressing, not for defining bytes. AFAIK it is like this in every 6502 assembler, not only WLA...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
