	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">.dw label<br /><br />is simpler than<br /><br />.db &lt;label, &gt;label</div>
<br />In this case, it would seem so. But sometimes it really is better to break lists of 16-bit values into 2 lists of 8-bit values (list of high bytes, list o low bytes), because of indexing. I'm sure everyone knows that, but I'm just pointing it out.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
